                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1111 Nelson, Bert N./77: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-03-17T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 17, 1931—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 17—3:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>23. The following telegram has been sent to the Legation: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“March 17, noon. I have received today the following telegram from Dr.
                            Skinsnes concerning Nelson and Tvedt: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>‘Letter from prisoners dated March 11th states health good, not
                                    further tortured, located Kenchiatawu 37 li east of
                                    Chiliping.’</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>Above information as regards location of captives has been communicated
                            to Chinese authorities.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Nanking and Department.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
